item.caption: CREATININE AND CALCULATED GLOMERULAR FILTRATION RATE (CREATININE, SERUM, WITH GLOMERULAR FILTRATION RATE, CALCULATED) - Final result (11/30/2012 12:40 PM PST)

content.content:
Glomerular Filtration Rate (GFR) estimate is expressed in mL/min/1.73 m2 body
surface area. A GFR estimate is validated only for patients greater than or
equal to 18 years of age. Since this test is not
useful if renal function is changing rapidly, a GFR estimate is not reported
for inpatients. Many elderly patients have mildly to moderately reduced GFR.
Per K/DOQI Clinical Practice Guidelines on Chronic Kidney Disease:
GFR 30 - 59 = Stage 3 CKD
GFR 15 - 29 = Stage 4 CKD
GFR <15 = Stage 5 CKD
